  "body": "**What this PR does / why we need it**:\r\n\r\nAdd possibility to put \"--safe\" argument to install and upgrade command that restores the state of cluster in case of failed install/upgrade attempt. \r\n\r\nThis resolves the problem of non-atomic upgrade process in helm and removes need to write scripts to handle failed deployments. Also, closes #3338.\r\n\r\n**Special notes for your reviewer**:\r\n\r\nThis is a proposal for such functionality, so I haven't any documentation and unit tests yet. However I've tested this functionality by hands on living cluster.\r\n\r\nAlso, I am not a professional Go developer, so if there are ways to improve implementation with fluent Go cunstructions, I would be glad for suggestions.\r\n\r\n**If applicable**:\r\n- [x] this PR contains documentation\r\n- [x] this PR contains unit tests\r\n- [ ] this PR has been tested for backwards compatibility\r\n",
